#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:156
msgid "Rename drm_atomic_state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:158
msgid ""
"The KMS framework uses two slightly different definitions for the ``state`` "
"concept. For a given object (plane, CRTC, encoder, etc., so "
"``drm_$OBJECT_state``), the state is the entire state of that object. "
"However, at the device level, ``drm_atomic_state`` refers to a state update "
"for a limited number of objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:164
msgid ""
"The state isn't the entire device state, but only the full state of some "
"objects in that device. This is confusing to newcomers, and "
"``drm_atomic_state`` should be renamed to something clearer like "
"``drm_atomic_commit``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:169
msgid ""
"In addition to renaming the structure itself, it would also imply renaming "
"some related functions (``drm_atomic_state_alloc``, "
"``drm_atomic_state_get``, ``drm_atomic_state_put``, "
"``drm_atomic_state_init``, ``__drm_atomic_state_free``, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:174 ../../../gpu/todo.rst:742
msgid "Contact: Maxime Ripard <mripard@kernel.org>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:179
msgid "Fallout from atomic KMS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:181
msgid ""
"``drm_atomic_helper.c`` provides a batch of functions which implement legacy "
"IOCTLs on top of the new atomic driver interface. Which is really nice for "
"gradual conversion of drivers, but unfortunately the semantic mismatches are "
"a bit too severe. So there's some follow-up work to adjust the function "
"interfaces to fix these issues:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:187
msgid ""
"atomic needs the lock acquire context. At the moment that's passed around "
"implicitly with some horrible hacks, and it's also allocate with "
"``GFP_NOFAIL`` behind the scenes. All legacy paths need to start allocating "
"the acquire context explicitly on stack and then also pass it down into "
"drivers explicitly so that the legacy-on-atomic functions can use them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:193
msgid ""
"Except for some driver code this is done. This task should be finished by "
"adding WARN_ON(!drm_drv_uses_atomic_modeset) in drm_modeset_lock_all()."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:196
msgid ""
"A bunch of the vtable hooks are now in the wrong place: DRM has a split "
"between core vfunc tables (named ``drm_foo_funcs``), which are used to "
"implement the userspace ABI. And then there's the optional hooks for the "
"helper libraries (name ``drm_foo_helper_funcs``), which are purely for "
"internal use. Some of these hooks should be move from ``_funcs`` to "
"``_helper_funcs`` since they are not part of the core ABI. There's a "
"``FIXME`` comment in the kerneldoc for each such case in ``drm_crtc.h``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:209
msgid "Move Buffer Object Locking to dma_resv_lock()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:211
msgid ""
"Many drivers have their own per-object locking scheme, usually using "
"mutex_lock(). This causes all kinds of trouble for buffer sharing, since "
"depending which driver is the exporter and importer, the locking hierarchy "
"is reversed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:216
msgid ""
"To solve this we need one standard per-object locking mechanism, which is "
"dma_resv_lock(). This lock needs to be called as the outermost lock, with "
"all other driver specific per-object locks removed. The problem is that "
"rolling out the actual change to the locking contract is a flag day, due to "
"struct dma_buf buffer sharing."
msgstr ""

