#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:271
msgid ""
"On at least x86-64, sys_imageblit() is significantly slower than "
"cfb_imageblit(), even though both use the same blitting algorithm and the "
"latter is written for I/O memory. It turns out that cfb_imageblit() uses "
"movl instructions, while sys_imageblit apparently does not. This seems to be "
"a problem with gcc's optimizer. DRM's format-conversion helpers might be "
"subject to similar issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:278
msgid ""
"Benchmark and optimize fbdev's sys_() helpers and DRM's format-conversion "
"helpers. In cases that can be further optimized, maybe implement a different "
"algorithm. For micro-optimizations, use movl/movq instructions explicitly. "
"That might possibly require architecture-specific helpers (e.g., storel() "
"storeq())."
msgstr ""

