#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:561
msgid "Make panic handling work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:563
msgid "This is a really varied tasks with lots of little bits and pieces:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:565
msgid ""
"The panic path can't be tested currently, leading to constant breaking. The "
"main issue here is that panics can be triggered from hardirq contexts and "
"hence all panic related callback can run in hardirq context. It would be "
"awesome if we could test at least the fbdev helper code and driver code by e."
"g. trigger calls through drm debugfs files. hardirq context could be "
"achieved by using an IPI to the local processor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:572
msgid ""
"There's a massive confusion of different panic handlers. DRM fbdev emulation "
"helpers had their own (long removed), but on top of that the fbcon code "
"itself also has one. We need to make sure that they stop fighting over each "
"other. This is worked around by checking ``oops_in_progress`` at various "
"entry points into the DRM fbdev emulation helpers. A much cleaner approach "
"here would be to switch fbcon to the `threaded printk support <https://lwn."
"net/Articles/800946/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:580
msgid ""
"``drm_can_sleep()`` is a mess. It hides real bugs in normal operations and "
"isn't a full solution for panic paths. We need to make sure that it only "
"returns true if there's a panic going on for real, and fix up all the "
"fallout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:585
msgid ""
"The panic handler must never sleep, which also means it can't ever "
"``mutex_lock()``. Also it can't grab any other lock unconditionally, not "
"even spinlocks (because NMI and hardirq can panic too). We need to either "
"make sure to not call such paths, or trylock everything. Really tricky."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:590
msgid ""
"A clean solution would be an entirely separate panic output support in KMS, "
"bypassing the current fbcon support. See `[PATCH v2 0/3] drm: Add panic "
"handling <https://lore.kernel.org/dri-devel/20190311174218.51899-1-"
"noralf@tronnes.org/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/todo.rst:594
msgid ""
"Encoding the actual oops and preceding dmesg in a QR might help with the "
"dread \"important stuff scrolled away\" problem. See `[RFC][PATCH] Oops "
"messages transfer using QR codes <https://lore.kernel.org/"
"lkml/1446217392-11981-1-git-send-email-alexandru.murtaza@intel.com/>`_ for "
"some example code that could be reused."
msgstr ""

